\title{Inner Regularity}
\date{2026-03-10}
\author{boat}
\taxon{Definition}
\import{math-lib}

\p{
A [Borel measure](gtop-000C) #{\mu} on a [topological space](gtop-0002) #{X} is \strong{inner regular} on a [Borel set](gtop-000L) #{E} if
##{
\mu(E) = \sup \set{ \mu(M) : M \subseteq E, \; M \text{ is compact} }
}
where #{M} is a [compact](gtop-0008) subset.
}

\p{
That is, the measure of #{E} can be approximated from below by the measures of [compact](gtop-0008) subsets of #{E}.
}
